	url = {https://www.science.org/doi/10.1126/science.1245813},
	doi = {10.1126/science.1245813},
	abstract = {Genetic and epigenetic studies of gene variants reveal a potential genomic target for treating hemoglobin disorders.
	
	[Also see Report by
	
	Bauer
	et al.
	
	]
	
	
	,
	
	Disorders of hemoglobins are the most common monogenic diseases in the world, with substantial morbidity and mortality resulting from either defective function of the protein, such as in sickle cell anemia, or from insufficient protein production, such as the thalassemias (
	
