	doi = {10.1093/molbev/msx286},
	abstract = {Tests of absolute model ﬁt are crucial in model-based inference because poorly structured models can lead to biased parameter estimates. In Bayesian inference, posterior predictive simulations can be used to test absolute model ﬁt. However, such tests have not been commonly practiced in phylogenetic inference due to a lack of convenient and ﬂexible software. Here, we describe our newly implemented tests of model ﬁt using posterior predictive testing, based on both data- and inference-based test statistics, in the phylogenetics software RevBayes. This new implementation makes a large spectrum of models available for use through a user-friendly and ﬂexible interface.},
